Subject: [PATCH 2/2] setup-wayland-base: explicit start dbus

Seems like elogind fails to properly pull in dbus. Work around it by
explicitly start dbus first.
---
 setup-wayland-base.in | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/setup-wayland-base.in b/setup-wayland-base.in
index 267c835..53a4a9e 100644
--- a/setup-wayland-base.in
+++ b/setup-wayland-base.in
@@ -30,7 +30,7 @@ apk add elogind polkit-elogind eudev "$@"
 
 setup-devd udev
 
-for service in elogind polkit; do
+for service in dbus elogind polkit; do
 	rc-service "$service" start
 	rc-update add "$service"
 done
